  "notes": "Keep. d1_far 53.1 %\u219290.8 % (+37.7 pts), S1 floor 100 %, zero regressions. Under the hardened harness: TAR@FAR=1 % is identical to run_015 across every scenario (98.4 % d1_far, 100 % d2/d3, 30.9 % within_clip, 79.9 % cross_camera, 100 % cross_session) because TAR@FAR is a property of the embeddings, not REMATCH. REMATCH=0.20 picks a more permissive operating point on the same ROC \u2014 admits more genuines (and more impostors) in the 0.20\u20130.30 cosine band. For SCface d1_far this lifts sr from 53 % to 91 % at the cost of unmeasured FAR in live deployment; sr=0.91 vs TAR@1 %=0.98 means the gap is now \u22127.6 pts (genuines admitted below the FAR=1 % threshold). Legitimate trade for re-id where a missed match is costlier than a rare false accept. Keep with caveat: run_017 could measure REMATCH=0.22 to land closer to the TAR@FAR=1 % sweet spot if a tighter FAR is desired. Audit vindication: within_clip_sanity\u2019s 97 % success_rate corresponds to TAR@FAR=1 %=31 %, confirming the prior \u201ctemporal_stability\u201d headline was ~65 pts of frame-leakage inflation and must not be cited as pose/distance invariance evidence again.",
